											<section class="main bio authorbio">
							<h3 class="invis">Author bio</h3>
																																															<a href="https://hakaimagazine.com/profiles/tommy-trenchard/" class="tagmanager" id="author_link_bottom" >
											<div class="container col3 ">
												<div class="col span2"><p>Tommy Trenchard is a freelance writer and photographer currently based in Cape Town, South Africa. His work focuses primarily on humanitarian issues in Africa and the Middle East, but he also regularly covers coastal communities around the world and their changing relationship with the ocean. These projects have taken him from sea cucumber ranches in Madagascar to Bajau stilt villages in Indonesia and longline fishing vessels in the mid-Atlantic.</p></div>
												<div class="singlebioimage col nomobile"><img width="520" height="520" src="https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/tommy-trenchard-520x520.jpg" class="attachment-medium size-medium wp-post-image" alt="Photographer Tommy Trenchard" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/tommy-trenchard-520x520.jpg 520w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/tommy-trenchard-150x150.jpg 150w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/tommy-trenchard-768x768.jpg 768w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/tommy-trenchard-900x900.jpg 900w, https://hakaimagazine.com/wp-content/uploads/tommy-trenchard.jpg 1000w" sizes="(max-width: 520px) 100vw, 520px" /></div>
											</div>
											</a>
																															</section>
										<hr class="fullwidth" />
										<section class="metadata main">
						<h3 class="invis">Tags</h3>
						<h4>Topic:</h4><ul class="articlecategories"><li><a href="https://hakaimagazine.com/topic/environments/" rel="tag">Environments</a>, </li><li><a href="https://hakaimagazine.com/topic/people-society/" rel="tag">People &amp; Society</a></li></ul>						<h4>Geographic Region:</h4><ul class="articlecategories"><li><a href="https://hakaimagazine.com/geographicregion/africa/" rel="tag">Africa</a></li></ul>						<h4>Oceanographic Region:</h4><ul class="articlecategories"><li><a href="https://hakaimagazine.com/oceanographicregion/atlantic-ocean/" rel="tag">Atlantic Ocean</a></li></ul>																													</section> 
